<li id="cite_note-forbesBList2007-4"><b><a href="#cite_ref-forbesBList2007_4-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web">[<a href="http://www.forbes.com/lists/2007/10/07billionaires_James-Simons_5GZ7.html" class="external free" title="http://www.forbes.com/lists/2007/10/07billionaires_James-Simons_5GZ7.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.forbes.com/lists/2007/10/07billionaires_James-Simons_5GZ7.html</a> "The World's Billionaires: #214 James Simons. Simons' most influential research involved the discovery and application of certain <a href="/wiki/Geometry" title="Geometry">geometric</a> measurements, and resulted in the <a href="/wiki/Chern-Simons_form" title="Chern-Simons form">Chern-Simons form</a> (aka Chern-Simons invariants, or <a href="/wiki/Chern-Simons_theory" title="Chern-Simons theory" class="mw-redirect">Chern-Simons theory</a>). In 1974, his theory was published in <i>Characteristic Forms and Geometric Invariants</i>, co-authored with the differential geometer <a href="/wiki/Shiing-Shen_Chern" title="Shiing-Shen Chern">Shiing-Shen Chern</a>. The theory has wide use in theoretical <a href="/wiki/Physics" title="Physics">physics</a>, particularly <a href="/wiki/String_theory" title="String theory">string theory</a>."]. Forbes.com. 2007-03-08<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.forbes.com/lists/2007/10/07billionaires_James-Simons_5GZ7.html" class="external free" title="http://www.forbes.com/lists/2007/10/07billionaires_James-Simons_5GZ7.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.forbes.com/lists/2007/10/07billionaires_James-Simons_5GZ7.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-05-02</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=The+World%27s+Billionaires%3A+%23214+James+Simons.++%0A%0ASimons%27+most+influential+research+involved+the+discovery+and+application+of+certain+%5B%5Bgeometry%7Cgeometric%5D%5D+measuremen